@node FONTLIST "Fontlist"

@{b}WW-Fontlist@{ub}

   This program makes a list of all fonts installed for Wordworth 6. (Version 5 should be possible.)

   Aminet: util/rexx/WW-Fontlist.lha

@endnode
@node DRUCK "Druck"

@{b}WW-Print@{ub}

   Print several documents one after another automatically. Wordworth 5 and 6.

   Aminet: util/rexx/WW-Print.lha

@endnode
@node FARBEN "Farben"

@{b}WW-Farben@{ub}

   Overview over the pre-defined colours of WW. (WW 3.0.-Document and ARexx-Script)
   As the colours are named in German, I don't know how WW will react if you load
   it with the English version. Maybe you have to work on it a bit. Please tell me!

   Aminet: docs/misc/WW-Farben.lha

@endnode
@node KAESTEN "Labels"

@{b}WW-Labels@{ub}

   As many text frames on a page as you like. Wordworth 5 and 6. So you can print labels etc.
   All parameters can be set; if you contact me, I will make a more comfortable version.
   (Only then!)

   Aminet: util/rexx/WW-Labels.lha
@endnode
@node KREISE "Kreise"
@{b}WW-Circles@{ub}

    Makes circles with the same centre. Wordworth 5 and 6.

    Aminet: util/rexx/WW-Circles.lha

@endnode
@node FKEYS "FKeys"
@{b}WW-FKeys@{ub}

    Overview over the F-Keys of Wordworth. Print it, cut it out and put it around your F-Keys.
    Apt for Amiga 1200. Wordworth 3.0.-document.
    Sorry, you have to translate it first; I don't know the English words for all these things.

    Aminet: docs/misc/WW-Fkeys.lha

@endnode
@node BIBEL "Bibel"
@{b}Bibel@{ub}

    Program that shows bible text in seconds and puts them in the clipboard.
    Needs:
    - Bibletext in ASCII
    - Golded 4
    - Muchmore
    Should be possible to adapt it for other long texts, e.g. laws.

    It works, but isn't ready yet, German only, contact @{"me" link Autor} if you are interested.


@endnode

